#META# shelfmark: Firuzkuh 68, recto
#META# collection: Afghanistan National Archives
#META# group: Firuzkuh Papers
#META# classification: Silver (given following internal peer review)
#META# primaryLanguage: New Persian (Arabic script)
#META# documentType: Letter
#META# writingSupport: paper
#META# writingSupportDetails: fold lines :: fraying/crumpling :: pasted into Mirza Khwaja Muhammad’s notebook :: tears
#META# writingSupportNotes: Incomplete, black ink
#META# foldLinesCount: 10
#META# foldLinesAlignment: horizontal
#META# contentSummary: Fragmentary letter seemingly about the theft of cropped wheat from a farm. The sender is expressing his innocence to the landlord on behalf of his community of gleaners, and suggests that others have been taking the wheat late at night. He says that if the landlord does not believe him and wants to punish them, they are willing to vacate the property.
